ort Unit''' (Cmdr. F.W. Howers)\n:: 3 [[destroyer escort]]s: ''[[USS Whitehurst|Whitehurst]]'', ''[[USS Witter|Witter]]'', ''[[USS Bowers|Bowers]]''\n: '''Leyte Gulf Unit''' (Capt. E.P. Hylant)\n:: 6 tankers: ''[[USS Arethusa (IX-135)|Arethusa]]'', ''[[USS Caribou|Caribou]]'', ''[[USS Mink|Mink]]'', ''[[USS Panda|Panda]]'', ''[[USS Porcupine (IX-126)|Porcupine]]'', {{flagdeco|Australia}} HMAS ''Bishopdale''\n:: 1 water tanker: ''[[USS Severn (AO-61)|Severn]]''\n:: 4 [[net tender]]s: ''[[USS Indus|Indus]]'', ''[[USS Teak|Teak]]'', ''[[USS Silverbell|Silverbell]]'', ''[[USS Satinleaf|Satinleaf]]''\n:: 3 repair and salvage vessels: ''[[USS Achilles (ARL-41)|Achilles]]'', ''[[USS Cable|Cable]]'', ''[[USS Midas|Midas]]''\n:: 1 [[Dry dock#Floating|floating dry dock]]: ''ARD-19''\n:: 4 [[ammunition ship]]s: ''[[USS Murzim|Murzim]]'', ''Poyang'', ''Ranvr'', ''Yunnan''\n:: 9 provision ships: ''[[USS Arequipa|Arequipa]]'', ''Calamaries'', ''[[USS Mizar (AF-12)|Mizar]]'', ''Octane'', ''[[USS Crux|Crux]]'', ''[[USS Ganymede|Ganymede]]'', ''[[USS Triangulum|Triangulum]]'', ''[[USS Pollux (AKS-4)|Pollux]]'', ''[[USS Acubens|Acubens]]'', {{flagdeco|Australia}} HMAS ''Merkur''\n:: 2 [[hospital ship]]s: ''[[USS Mercy (AH-8)|Mercy]]'', ''[[USS Comfort (AH-6)|Comfort]]''\n\n== US Third Fleet ==\n{{multiple image\n | direction = horizontal\n | width = 160\n | header = Third Fleet and Fast Carrier commanders\n | image1 = W_Halsey.jpg\n | caption1 = Admiral William F. Halsey, Jr.\n | image2 = Vice Admiral Marc A. Mitscher during World War II (80-G-424169).jpg\n | caption2 = Vice Adm. Marc A. Mitscher\n}}\nAdmiral [[William F. Halsey]] in fast battleship ''[[USS New Jersey|New Jersey]]''\n\n=== [[Fast Carrier Task Force|Fast Carrier Force]] (Task Force 38) ===\nVice Admiral [[Marc A. Mitscher]] in fleet carrier ''[[USS Lexington (CV-16)|Lexington]]\n\n==== Task Group 38.1 ====\n[[File:Vice-Admiral_John_S_McCain.jpg|160px|thumb|right|Vice Adm. John S. McCain]]\n[[File:USS_Cowpens_(CVL-25)_at_sea_on_31_August_1944.jpg|220px|thumb|Light carrier ''Cowpens'']]\n\nVice Admiral [[John S. McCain Sr.|John S. McCain]]\n\n:'''2 fleet carriers'''\n:: [[USS Hornet (CV-12)|''Hornet'']] (Capt. A.K. Doyle)\n::: ''Air Group 11'' (Cmdr. F.R. Schrader)\n::: VF-11: 33 [[F6F Hellcat]] fighters, 4 [[Grumman F6F Hellcat#Further development|F6F-xN Hellcat]] night fighters\n::: VB-11: 25 [[SB2C Helldiver]] dive bombers\n::: VT-11: &nbsp;&nbsp;1 [[TBF Avenger]], 17 [[TBM Avenger]] torpedo bombers\n:: [[USS Wasp (CV-18)|''Wasp'']] (Capt. O.A. Weller)\n::: ''Air Group 14'' (Cmdr. W.C. Wingard)\n::: VF-14: 38 [[F6F Hellcat]] fighters, 4 [[Grumman F6F Hellcat#Further development|F6F-xN Hellcat]] night fighters\n::: VB-14: 10 [[F6F Hellcat]] fighters, 25 [[SB2C Helldiver]] dive bombers\n::: VT-14: &nbsp;&nbsp;6 [[TBF Avenger]], 12 [[TBM Avenger]] torpedo bombers\n\n:'''2 light carriers'''\n:: [[USS Monterey (CVL-26)|''Monterey'']] (Capt. S.H. Ingersoll)\n::: ''Air Group 28'' (Lt. Cmdr. R.W. Mehle):\n::: VF-28: 23 [[F6F Hellcat]] fighters\n::: VT-28: &nbsp;&nbsp;9 [[TBM Avenger]] torpedo bombers\n:: [[USS Cowpens (CVL-25)|''Cowpens'']] (Capt. H.W. Taylor)\n::: ''Air Group 22'' (Lt. Cmdr. T.H. Jenkins):\n::: VF-22: 26 [[F6F Hellcat]] fighters\n::: VT-22: &nbsp;&nbsp;9 [[TBM Avenger]] torpedo bombers\n\n:'''Cruiser Division 6''' (Rear Admiral [[C. Turner Joy]])\n:: 1 heavy cruiser: ''[[USS Wichita|Wichita]]'' (Capt. D.A. Spencer)\n\n:'''Cruiser Division 10''' (Rear Admiral L.J. Wiltse)\n:: 2 heavy cruisers: ''[[USS Boston|Boston]]'' (Capt. E.E. Herrmann), ''[[USS Canberra|Canberra]]'' (Capt. A.R. Early)\n:: 1 light cruiser: ''[[USS Houston|Houston]]'' (Capt. W.W. Behrens)\n\n:'''Screen''' (Capt.C.F. Espe)\n:: 15 destroyers\n::: 13 [[Fletcher class destroyer|Fletcher-class]]: [[USS Izard (DD-589)|''Izard'']], [[USS Charrette (DD-581)|''Charrette'']], [[USS Conner (DD-582)|''Conner'']], ''[[USS Bell (DD-587)|Bell]]'', [[USS Burns (DD-588)|''Burns'']], [[USS Cogswell|''Cogswell'']], [[USS Caperton|''Caperton'']], [[USS Ingersoll|''Ingersoll'']], [[USS Knapp|''Knapp'']], [[USS Boyd (DD-544)|''Boyd'']], ''[[USS Cowell (DD-547)|''Cowell'']], ''[[USS Brown (DD-546)|Brown]]'', ''[[USS Woodworth|Woodworth]]''\n::: 2 [[Gleaves-class destroyer|Gleaves class]]: ''[[USS McCalla|McCalla]]'', ''[[USS Grayson|Grayson]]''\n\n==== Task Group 38.2 ====\n[[File:Vice Admiral Gerald F. Bogan aboard USS Valley Forge (CV-45).jpg|420px|right|thumb|Rear Adm. Gerald F. Bogan]]\n[[File:USS Intrepid (CV-11) underway off Newport News on 16 August 1943 (NH 53254).jpg|220px|right|thumb|Fleet carrier ''Intrepid'']]\n[[File:USS_Bunker_Hill_(CV-17)_at_sea_in_1945_(NH_42373).jpg|220px|thumb|Fleet carrier ''Bunker Hill'']]\n[[File:USS_Iowa_(BB-61).jpg|220px|right|thumb|[[Iowa-class battleship]]|Iowa-class fast battleship ''Iowa'']]\n\nRear Admiral [[Gerald F. Bogan]]\n\n:'''3 fleet carriers'''\n:: ''[[USS Intrepid (CV-11)|Intrepid]]'' (Capt. J.F. Bolger)\n::: ''Air Group 18'' (Cmdr. W.E. Ellis)\n::: VF-18: 38 [[F6F Hellcat]] fighters, 5 [[Grumman F6F Hellcat#Further development|F6F-xN Hellcat]] night fighters\n::: VB-18: 28 [[SB2C Helldiver]] dive bombers\n::: VT-18: 18 [[TBM Avenger]] torpedo bombers\n:: ''[[USS Hancock (CV-19)|Hancock]]'' (Capt. F.C. Dickey)\n::: ''Air Group 7'' (Cmdr. J.D. Lamade)\n::: VF-7: 37 [[F6F Hellcat]] fighters, 4 [[Grumman F6F Hellcat#Further development|F6F-xN Hellcat]] night fighters\n::: VB-7: 42 [[SB2C Helldiver]] dive bombers\n::: VT-7: 18 [[TBM Avenger]] torpedo bombers\n:: ''[[USS Bunker Hill (CV-17)|Bunker Hill]]'' (Capt. M.R. Greer)\n::: ''Air Group 8'' (Cmdr. R.L. Shifley)\n::: VF-8: 40 [[F6F Hellcat]] fighters, 8 [[Grumman F6F Hellcat#Further development|F6F-xN Hellcat]] night fighters\n::: VB-8: 17 [[SB2C Helldiver]], 3 [[SBF Helldiver]], 4 [[SBW Helldiver]]  dive bombers\n::: VT-8: 19 [[TBM Avenger]] torpedo bombers\n\n:'''2 light carriers'''\n:: ''[[USS Cabot (CVL-28)|Cabot]]'' (Capt. S.J. Michael)\n::: ''Air Group 29'' (Lt. Cmdr. W.E. Eder)\n::: VF-29: 21 [[F6F Hellcat]] fighters\n::: VT-29: &nbsp;&nbsp;1 [[TBF Avenger]], 8 [[TBM Avenger]] torpedo bombers\n:: ''[[USS Independence (CVL-22)|Independence]]'' (Capt. E.C. Ewen)\n::: ''Night Air Group 41'' (Cmdr. T.F. Caldwell)\n::: VFN-41: &nbsp;&nbsp;5 [[F6F Hellcat]] fighters, 14 [[Grumman F6F Hellcat#Further development|F6F-xN Hellcat]] night fighters\n::: VTN-41: &nbsp;&nbsp;8 [[TBM Avenger]] torpedo bombers\n\n:'''Battleship Division 7''' (Rear Admiral Oscar C. Badger)\n:: 2 fast battleships: ''[[USS Iowa (BB-61)|Iowa]]'' (Capt. A.R. McCann), ''[[USS New Jersey (BB-62)|New Jersey]]'' (Capt. C.F. Holden)\n\n:'''Cruiser Division 14''' (Rear Admiral F.E.M. Whiting)\n:: 2 light cruisers: ''[[USS Vincennes (CL-64)|Vincennes]]'' (Capt. A.D. Brown), ''[[USS Miami (CL-89)|Miami]]'' (Capt. J.G. Crawford)\n:: 2 [[light cruiser#Atlanta-class cruiser|anti-aircraft light cruiser]]s:{{efn|These cruisers were intended as destroyer leaders when designed. After the first two to be used in this role, ''[[USS Atlanta (CL-51)|Atlanta]]'' and ''[[USS Juneau (CL-52)|Juneau]]'', were lost at the [[Naval Battle of Guadalcanal]], this mission was abandoneded and the anti-aircraft mission adopted.<ref>Stille, p. 7.</ref>}} ''[[USS San Diego (CL-53)|San Diego]]'' (Capt. W.A. Mullan), ''[[USS Oakland (CL-95)|Oakland]]'' (Capt. K.S. Reed)\n\n:'''Screen''' (Captain J.P. Womble)\n:: 18 destroyers (all [[Fletcher class destroyer|Fletcher-class]]): ''[[USS Owen (DD-536)|''Owen'']], ''[[USS Miller (DD-535)|''Miller'']], [[USS The Sullivans (DD-537)|''The Sullivans'']], [[USS Stephen Potter (DD-538)|''Stephen Potter'']], [[USS Tingey (DD-539)|''Tingey'']], [[USS Hickox (DD-673)|''Hickox'']], [[USS Hunt (DD-674)|''Hunt'']], [[USS Lewis Hancock (DD-675)|''Lewis Hancock'']], [[USS Marshall (DD-676)|''Marshall'']], [[USS Halsey Powell|''Halsey Powell'']], [[USS Cushing (DD-797)|''Cushing'']], ''[[USS Colahan|Colahan]]'', ''[[USS Uhlmann|Uhlmann]]'', ''[[USS Benham (DD-796)|Benham]]'', 